I should clarify terminology:

This variant was first identified in the UK...it may not have originated there. 

The UK does a ton of genomic analyses and is primed to detect novel variants. 

The more technical abbreviation for this SARS-CoV-2 variant is "B.1.1.7"

Cases of new #SARSCoV2 strain spreading rapidly in the UK have been confirmed in Denmark 🇩🇰, Italy 🇮🇹, Gibraltar 🇬🇮, Netherlands 🇳🇱 Australia 🇦🇺 . Possibly France 🇫🇷 and South Africa 🇿🇦.
